File: In a statement, Eskom said they continue to monitor a volatile system and updated the country on generation breakdowns and how the system is faring at the beginning of the week. JOHANNESBURG - Eskom will be implementing load reduction in areas of the Free State, Mpumalanga, Limpopo and KwaZulu-Natal. The load reduction will take place between 5pm and 10pm on Monday. READ: Eskom suspends load-shedding In Limpopo, customers in Mopani Districts will be affected. In the Free State, Thabo Mofutsanyana District and Lejweleputswa District will be experiencing load reduction. KwaZulu-Natal and Mpumalanga will also be experiencing power cuts.